{"sectionId":647,"sectionIdLiteral":"647","humanId":"lesson-234","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Father, today I am Your Son again.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 234"},"annotation":"W-234","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-234\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"647#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Today we will anticipate the time when dreams of sin and guilt are gone, and we have reached the holy peace we never left.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Merely a tiny instant has elapsed between eternity and timelessness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>So brief the interval there was no lapse in continuity, nor break in thoughts which are forever unified as one.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Nothing has ever happened to disturb the peace of God the Father and the Son.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>This we accept as wholly true today.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"647#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>We thank You, Father, that we cannot lose the memory of You and of Your Love.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"647#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>We recognize our safety, and give thanks for all the gifts You have bestowed on us, for all the loving help we have received, for Your eternal patience, and the Word which You have given us that we are saved.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Today we will anticipate the time when dreams of sin and guilt are gone, and we have reached the holy peace we never left. Merely a tiny instant has elapsed between eternity and timelessness. So","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 234: Father, today I am Your Son again | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Co